

11/15/2022 - OOP Recap

Object Oriented Programming:
* Converting real life problems into programming objects and using them.

Example: 
*Creating a google home page
	GoogleHomePage
		1. Constructor -> creating the object of the class
		2. Instance Variables(Fields, States, Attributes...) -> 
		Defining the values of the object that we are creating
			* Logo
			* SearchBar
			* SignInButton
		3. Methods (Functions,...)-> What does this object do?
			* Signing in
			* Searching 
			* Going to settings
		4. Code blocks(static/non-static/local) -> Perform an action before anyting else





